@ParitoshBh Snap is like LXC so it's not a solution when you have dedicated server to run podman
In that case, why not running podman in VM using Fedora ?

@mheon Are you referring to [Open Build Service](https://openbuildservice.org/) ? Have you any ETA about when it'll be okay for prod because deleting good container to after restart them, it's a little overkill and bad experience for user "pro-Docker" when I force migration to podman.
